      "t": "p",
      "x": "ReClaude A: Decide by cell type and what increased. Cardiac myocytes are permanent and cannot divide, so a pressure-loaded heart can only enlarge existing cells (hypertrophy, more actin/myosin). The thyroid and prostate epithelium CAN divide, so they add cells (hyperplasia, increased number). The tissue's divisional capacity forces which adaptation is even possible."
