      "t": "p",
      "x": "NECROPTOSIS and PYROPTOSIS — know the one-liners. Jones flagged these as lighter-touch, so travel light. Necroptosis is a hybrid: it is programmed and uses a signaling cascade (RIPK1/RIPK3 → MLKL) like apoptosis, but it is caspase-independent and ends in necrosis-style membrane rupture with inflammation — \"programmed necrosis.\" Pyroptosis is the even briefer mention: an inflammasome/caspase-1-driven death that releases IL-1 and screams for inflammation, classically in response to intracellular microbes. For this exam, the contrast that earns points is apoptosis (silent, intact) versus everything necrotic (spilled, inflammatory)."
