   "Exudate vs transudate is the highest-yield discrimination. Exudate = protein-RICH, cellular, from increased permeability — always tied to inflammation. Transudate = protein-POOR, few cells, from a hydrostatic/oncotic pressure problem (heart failure, nephrotic syndrome) — NOT inflammation. “Link exudate WITH inflammation.”",
