      "x": "ReClaude A: Redness and warmth are FLOW signs — arteriolar vasodilation (histamine, prostaglandins, bradykinin) raising blood flow. Swelling is a PERMEABILITY sign — increased postcapillary venule permeability (histamine-driven endothelial contraction) producing a protein-rich exudate. Pain is bradykinin + PGE2 on nerve endings; loss of function is the combined tissue effect."
