      "x": "OVERVIEW. Vila treated the causes of inflammation largely through the lens of which leukocytosis points to which cause — a reference-style pairing rather than a deep mechanism. The system recognizes trouble two ways: it detects microbes (via pattern-recognition receptors that later lectures expand) and it detects damaged or necrotic cells (the danger signals released by dying tissue, e.g., the neutrophil influx into an infarct where there is no infection at all)."
