      "t": "p",
      "x": "OVERVIEW. Activated leukocytes are not precision weapons — the ROS, NO, and proteases they release to kill microbes also injure host tissue, which is the functio laesa of the cardinal signs and the basis of much inflammatory disease. So the response must be actively terminated. Anti-inflammatory mediators — IL-10 and TGF-β — switch it off, and short-lived neutrophils die once the stimulus clears."
