      "t": "p",
      "x": "OVERVIEW. Cytokines are low-molecular-weight proteins secreted by activated cells — a broad family that Vila grouped as interleukins, chemokines, interferons, growth factors, and the proinflammatory cytokines. Two of them sit at the center of acute inflammation: interleukin-1 (IL-1) and tumor necrosis factor (TNF)."
