      "x": "THE DISORDER CLASSES. Disorders sort into single-gene (one mutation, e.g., CFTR), chromosomal (whole-segment changes), complex/multifactorial (many genes + environment), and mitochondrial. The mitochondrial class has a board-favorite quirk: because mitochondrial DNA sits in the mitochondria — not the nuclear chromosomes — it is always inherited from the mother, since the egg keeps its mitochondrial DNA at fertilization while sperm mitochondria are lost."
