      "x": "WHY SANGER FAILS FOR COMMON DISEASE. Sanger looks at one region at a time, so it can’t handle polygenic, multifactorial disease. As Reindel put it, diabetes isn’t caused by one mutation — many genes plus environment raise the risk — so narrowing to a single gene misses the picture. This limitation is the whole reason next-generation sequencing exists."
