      "x": "OVERVIEW. Prediction is a different job from diagnosis. A genetic marker is a DNA sequence at a known physical location that statistically associates with a higher probability of disease — that association is what makes it a predictive or prognostic tool, even when the marker isn’t the direct cause. The central reframing of this LO is Reindel’s recurring point that most common diseases are polygenic, not monogenic."
