      "t": "p",
      "x": "VIRAL LOAD — the CT-value inverse. Quantitative PCR (qPCR) monitors viral load (HIV, hepatitis B/C, COVID). The readout to memorize is the cycle-threshold (CT) value, and it is inversely related to viral load: the lower the CT, the higher the load. Mechanistically, a low CT means a positive signal appeared after very few amplification cycles — which only happens when there’s abundant starting template. Chawla recalled COVID-lab samples reading CT ~35–37 toward the end of the infection cycle (low load, recovering). Read it forward and you’ll get it exactly backwards, which is the trap."
