      "x": "OVERVIEW. Bonfil spent only a couple of minutes here, so keep it light. Not all of cancer is changes to the DNA sequence — some changes regulate gene expression without altering the sequence at all. These are epigenetic changes, and three mechanisms are worth recognizing: histone modification (altering how tightly DNA is packed, changing transcription), microRNAs (non-coding RNAs that bind messenger RNAs and block"
