      "x": "THE EXCHANGE UNIT — your baseline. The alveolus is lined by type I pneumocytes (flat cells covering ~95% of the surface, where gas exchange happens) and type II pneumocytes (cuboidal, make surfactant to prevent alveolar collapse, and serve as the stem cell that differentiates into type I after injury). The conducting airway — the tracheobronchial tree — is different histology: pseudostratified ciliated epithelium with goblet cells and cartilage. Hold this baseline, because every viral injury below is a deviation from it."
