      "x": "CMV — the virus of falling immunity. Cytomegalovirus is the herpesvirus to attach to the immunocompromised. It stays latent and reactivates when cell-mediated immunity drops — transplant recipients, AIDS patients — producing interstitial pneumonitis, colitis, and retinitis. The cytopathic tell is the one from LO 19.5: a markedly enlarged cell (cytomegaly) with a single large basophilic intranuclear owl’s-eye inclusion plus a clear halo, sometimes with small cytoplasmic inclusions too. On a CMV-pneumonitis slide you’ll see those enlarged cells scattered in the alveolar"
