      "x": "OVERVIEW — the bacterial spine, and Vila’s confirmed exam format. This is the broadest objective in the block, and Vila calls it “one of the hardest lectures to teach because there’s so many things.” Her exam format — confirmed explicitly when a student asked — is the organizing principle: “a lot of your question stems are going to have the clinical presentation, signs and symptoms, and then matching that to the disease or the causative agent.” So read every staph/strep syndrome below as a presentation → organism pairing, often anchored by an image."
